annotation.TEXT: And now, 2-1-2 is 100% complete! Next time, I'll be taking on 2-1-3, which I think will be a boss level...
Aww... So close.
Oh, man. Some tricky-looking stars here.
I still don't know what the purpose of the stuff up there is...
Meh. I guess there's no need to kill that green FOE up there. He's usually too far off screen to shoot at me.
Alright, now that I know about the bricks with stars on them below, this part is much less scary to me.
MULTI KILL!
Oh, wait! That's all 100 stars! Argh, if it wasn't for those evil green FOEs in that pair of pipes early on, I could've perfected this on my first try!
Actually, there's three, as well as the goal.
Also, what about all that other stuff I saw in the sky throughout the level? ...Oh, maybe they're related to the secret exit!
Wow, that secret exit was tricky. I'm pretty sure I got lucky in a couple places.
Okay, I'm going to try to see if I can reach that checkpoint from here with the help of this duder.
Nothing too terribly tricky with the stars that I've seen so far, but I bet there are some way up above that I'm going to miss.
Blind jump!
Nuts! Okay, maybe I can get up there from here by using this blue guy.
This part's a little scary, though.
I guess I could've drill stomped my way down from up there, but I didn't know that I would want to drill stomp...
Awesome! I've pretty much got this now!
Come on, I'm barely tapping the jump button here.
Oh, I saw that. I know there's a mole FOE over there now.
What the french toast?! Okay, you all saw that I totally drill stomped that guy, right?
Okay, whew. The platform is visible from here. Thank goodness.
Whoa, careful!
Yeah, the next jump is a blind one, since I cannot see my next target from here.
Whoa, whoops! Okay, you can't drill stomp while holding something! (I intended to drill stomp on the green guys there, but that obviously didn't happen.)
And there you go! This level is now perfected! However, I'm not quite done with it yet...
Whoa, whoops. My name isn't "SRQ". How silly.
So many blind jumps! I vaguely remember this part from when raocow did it, though.
Oh, man. There's totally gotta be something up here.
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marisa World! So, let's see what the next level in Sky World has to offer...
Okay, I dispatched the HB FOE and a few other duders quickly, and I found a miko suit.
Alright, I've hit the checkpoint. Now, I'm guessing that the secret exit will be up in the air to the right.
Aha, I thought there might be some starts up there above the star... Er, I mean, some stars up there above the start.
Alright, now let's finally advance past the first screen.
There we go.
World 2-1-2 start!
Yes, made it! Woo-hoo!
Up next is a Hammer Bro. FOE. Also, I thought I saw a blue duder up above.
Bah, stupid blue guy... But I'm up! Okay, let's hope I don't screw this up...
Okay, I'm on solid ground, and there's a some Lay's Wavy FOEs coming my way...
Okay, it's good that I now know about those bricks with the stars on them down there, for when I go for the perfect later.
4 attempts later...
Oh, no. Please do not tell me that I'm going to have to blindly land on that red platform!
Whoa! Well, it's a good thing I was carrying a duder there!
Okay, that was a reckless blind jump, which didn't accomplish much, aside from letting me see that there are duders up there that I'm probably meant to bounce off of.
Bah, that was a dumb hit. Also, the game froze briefly because I accidentally hit the Alt key while fumbling there.
That was almost dangerous.
GIGA DRILL BREAK!!!
I'm glad I didn't hastily kill this guy.
D'oh! I didn't mean to kill that guy! Well, there's more guys coming up that I can use, so don't panic.
DOUBLE KILL!
To be continued... Ze!
Yeah, I kept having dumb deaths early on, and I want to at least reach the checkpoint on that blue platform without dying, to maximize my chances at the tricky stuff past it.
Got one of them, barely. Okay, maybe I can get the other one on my next try.
Ooh, nice shot. Got rid of that green monster with that one.
Can't quite reach that cloud. Maybe I can just bounce straight to the blue platform with the checkpoint, though.
0 attempts later...
There's a blue guy and a cloud with a yellow guy up there...
Yep, there's a secret exit to find. Well, I'm going to go for the perfect first, since I found all the stars already.
Alright, let's just wait for this guy to wake up.
Really, game? They were down inside their pipes when I dropped down this time? Why couldn't that have been the case the first time?
Oh, hey there, Chuck FOE! Do you want to help me get up there? Thanks!
Well, there's a checkpoint, so perhaps I'll naturally end up there later, but I don't know...
I probably won't want to be too hasty in killing everything, in case I need a duder for a boost... like right here, perhaps.
But wait, there's more? Hmm... Maybe I have to bring another guy with me to bounce off of here, or maybe there's another way up there...
DIE, YOU EVIL PIECE OF BAD PUDDING!!!
Heck, yeah! I don't know if I just sequence broke, or found a route leading to a secret, though.
Ugh... I think I hit a glitch where the game thought I hit the pipe before I hit the FOE, because it was sinking into the pipe at the moment, and I hit them at the same time.
No need to reach that checkpoint platform up there this time, since there aren't any stars up there, and if I die, I'll restart the whole level anyway.
Oh, come on! That's just not fair! I had no way of knowing that I'd be landing on green guys there!
Excellent. The highest potato chip FOE at the start is the best one for getting those stars with.
...Assuming I can aim right...
Erg, not quite high enough. Let me make the duders respawn and try again...
